- "Single A" when B1 = "Description A" and B2 is blank,
- "Single B" when B1 = "Description B" and B2 is blank,
- "Multiple" when B1 = "Description A" and B2 = "Description B".

We will overwrite D1 with a single IF/AND formula that covers these three cases (and returns an empty string otherwise). After writing the formula, we will save the workbook to the output directory, run recalculation, and verify the result in D1.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter
import os

# Paths
input_path = '/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_51249_init.xlsx'
output_dir = '/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/'
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, '1_51249_init.xlsx')

# Load workbook (keep formulas)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]

# Write the required formula into D1
formula = (
    '=IF(AND(B1="Description A",B2=""),"Single A",'
    'IF(AND(B1="Description B",B2=""),"Single B",'
    'IF(AND(B1="Description A",B2="Description B"),"Multiple","")))'
)
ws['D1'].value = formula

# Save workbook to output location
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas
await recalculate(output_path)

# Reload with data_only to verify the computed value
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_check = wb_check[wb_check.sheetnames[0]]
print('D1 after recalculation:', ws_check['D1'].value)
```
